headline.main: FROM OREGON.; The Snake Indians--Failure of the Expodition Againet Them--Business in Oregon.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Expedition sent out to chastise the Snake Indians returned about three weeks ago, having accomplished little or nothing. A few defenceless, and perhaps innocent Indians, were taken prisoners, and three or four were shot in attempting to escape.

headline.main: FROM THE CRIMEA.; Interesting Letter from an Officer in the Allied Army.

docs.lead_paragraph: The following interesting letter has been forwarded to us by our London Correspondent. It comes from high authority, and is statements are worthy of attention : BALAKLAVA, Wednesday, Nov. 8, 1854. Sebastopol is still not taken. I account for it by the following reasons : First, There is no Commander-in-Chief with full powers invested in his own hands.

headline.main: EUROPEAN AFFAIRS.; Condition, Prospects and Incidents of the Eastern War. Additional Extracts from our European Exchanges. A Result of the War---English Exaitation over the Alliauce with France.

docs.lead_paragraph: Not among the least remarkable, but certainly among the most agreeable results of the present war, is the tone which the greater part of the French press has taken with regard to England.

headline.main: Money and other Matters in Boston.

docs.lead_paragraph: Christmas will be more generally observed in this city, on Monday, than heretofore. Our money market was comparatively easy today, considering that the notes due at the banks previous to Tuesday has to be met to-day. The rates of interest in the street were from 1 1/2 to 2 percent. per month, for good paper. The financial prospects in this city are brightening.

headline.main: NEW-JERSEY.; Items of Texas News--Emigration--Agriculture--Prices of Provisions, &c. Measures for the Relief of the Poor in Jersey City.

docs.lead_paragraph: There are about 400 men out a employment residing in Jersey City, of which number probably two-thirds are heads of families. Many of these are in need of aid.
